Safety Competitive Analysis - RSV (Arexvy) vs RSV (Abrysvo)

1 Executive Summary

At the data lock point of 27 oct. 2023 in VAERS restricted to the United States, there were 902 spontaneous reports for RSV (AREXVY) and 448 spontaneous reports for RSV (ABRYSVO). So far, RSV (AREXVY) represents 66.9% of the RSV reports received.

In the demographic section, there is a comparison of the demographic characteristics (age, sex, states) of the spontaneous reports between RSV (AREXVY) and RSV (ABRYSVO). Distribution of age and sex are similar. Some geographical differences are noted and are probably due to differences in distribution: Florida and California are relatively higher contributors of reports for Arexvy while Ohio and Pennsylvannia are relatively higher contributors for Abrysvo.

In the disproportionality section, the MedDRA PTs with the highest differences in terms of disproportionality were highlighted. If using a threshold of 2 on an unstratified EBGM, there are 3 signals of disproportionate reporting for Arexvy: Product use issue, Product preparation issue, Exposure during pregnancy (19 cases of exposure to pregnancy - Arexvy was not approved for pregnant women while Abrysvo was). There is only 1 signal of disproportionality for Abrysvo: Incorrect route of product administration.

Let also note that Rash post Arexvy has an unexpected time-to-onset distribution.
